黑金企业

2
00:02:11,697 --> 00:02:17,498
1898年

3
00:04:56,961 --> 00:04:58,485
不!
No!

4
00:05:31,697 --> 00:05:33,961
找到了、找到了
There she is. There she is.

5
00:05:43,242 --> 00:05:44,800
找到了
There she is.

6
00:06:48,406 --> 00:06:51,432
“金银成份分析”

7
00:06:56,615 --> 00:07:03,543
“丹尼尔普兰优”

8
00:07:12,730 --> 00:07:17,225
1902年

9
00:14:33,371 --> 00:14:35,363
各位女士先生
Ladies and gentlemen,

10
00:14:35,474 --> 00:14:39,604
我至今已走遍北达克达州大半土地
I've traveled over half our state to be here tonight.

11
00:14:39,745 --> 00:14:42,235
由于新油井的开凿，我来晚了点
I couldn't get away sooner because my new well was coming in

12
00:14:42,380 --> 00:14:45,248
我得去监督一下
at Coyote Hills and I had to see about it.

13
00:14:45,384 --> 00:14:48,375
那口井现在日产两千桶油
That well is now flowing at 2,000 barrels

14
00:14:48,519 --> 00:14:51,682
每周都给我带来五千美元进帐
and it's paying me an income of $5,000 a week.

15
00:14:52,356 --> 00:14:55,655
我还在安特洛有16口量产油井
l have two others drilling and l have 16 producing at Antelope,

16
00:14:55,760 --> 00:15:00,197
各位女士先生，若我说我是油商，你们也会同意
so, ladies and gentlemen,
if l say l'm an oilman, you will agree.

17
00:15:03,034 --> 00:15:05,697
现在，你们有了绝佳的机会
Now, you have a great chance here,

18
00:15:05,803 --> 00:15:08,705
但一不小心还是会赔光本钱
but bear in mind you could lose it all if you're not careful.

19
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:11,206
在所有凿井碰运气的人之中
Out of all men that beg for a chance to drill your lots,

20
00:15:11,409 --> 00:15:14,538
也许20个有1个能成为油商
maybe one in twenty will be oilmen.

21
00:15:14,645 --> 00:15:15,874
剩下的都是投机客
The rest will be speculators,

22
00:15:15,980 --> 00:15:18,471
所以才有人会介入你们和油商间
that's men trying to get between you and the oilmen

23
00:15:18,616 --> 00:15:22,211
赚取那些原本应属于你们的钱
to get some of the money that ought, by rights, come to you.

24
00:15:22,321 --> 00:15:25,255
就算你们找到的人有钱又想凿井
Even if you find one that has money and means to drill,

25
00:15:25,389 --> 00:15:27,789
他也可能对于凿井一无所知
he'll maybe know nothing about drilling.

26
00:15:27,926 --> 00:15:29,894
那样他就得雇请人手
He'll have to hire the job out on contract,

27
00:15:29,995 --> 00:15:32,793
接着你们就得指望包工
and then you're depending on a contractor,

28
00:15:32,931 --> 00:15:33,989
他的动作俐落纯熟
who'll rush the job through

29
00:15:34,099 --> 00:15:36,192
找新工作就跟他的动作一样快
so he can get another contract just as quick as he can.

30
00:15:36,301 --> 00:15:37,859
这一行就是这样
This is the way that this works.

31
00:15:37,969 --> 00:15:41,234
你出多少？别浪费时间
What is your offer? We're wasting time.

32
00:15:41,505 --> 00:15:42,529
请安静
Please!

33
00:15:45,744 --> 00:15:47,677
我自己凿井
l do my own drilling.

34
00:15:48,312 --> 00:15:52,215
我的手下就是我的手下，他们也是我熟识的人
And the men that work for me,
work for me, and they are men l know.

35
00:15:52,317 --> 00:15:56,048
我认真经营，也谨慎监督
l make it my business to be there and to see their work.

36
00:15:56,153 --> 00:15:59,213
我不会乱扔工具，又到处乱找
l don't lose my tools in the hole
and spend months fishing for them.

37
00:15:59,390 --> 00:16:00,517
我不会敲坏水泥
l don't botch the cementing off

38
00:16:00,625 --> 00:16:04,186
让水流进洞里，搞砸整块地
and let water in the hole and ruin the whole lease.

39
00:16:04,296 --> 00:16:06,287
我是个爱家的人
l'm a family man.

40
00:16:06,431 --> 00:16:11,027
我经营的是家族事业，这是我儿子兼伙伴，H.W.普兰优
l run a family business. This is my son
and my partner, H.W. Plainview.

41
00:16:12,037 --> 00:16:16,837
少有油商能有如此家族伙伴关系
We offer you the bond of family that very few oilmen can understand.

42
00:16:18,809 --> 00:16:21,870
在这一行，只有我是如此做事
l'm fixed like no other company in this field

43
00:16:22,047 --> 00:16:25,174
因为我的灰狼坡油井已开始量产
and that's because my Coyote Hills well has just come in.

44
00:16:25,317 --> 00:16:27,750
我有一组设备随时准备上线
l have a string of tools all ready to put to work.

45
00:16:27,885 --> 00:16:30,013
一周内就能运送整组设备过来
l can load a rig onto trucks and have them here in a week.

46
00:16:30,121 --> 00:16:33,182
钻油井的木头我有熟人会帮忙
l have business connections,
so l can get the lumber for the derricks.

47
00:16:33,357 --> 00:16:37,088
时间这么赶，得靠朋友帮忙
Such things go by friendship in a rush like this.

48
00:16:37,229 --> 00:16:41,062
因此我也敢保证能动手钻探
And this is why l can guarantee to start drilling

49
00:16:41,198 --> 00:16:44,134
并提供现金来证明我说的话
and to put up the cash to back my word.

50
00:16:44,235 --> 00:16:45,793
我向各位保证
l assure you, ladies and gentlemen,

51
00:16:45,903 --> 00:16:49,202
不管其他人保证要怎么做
no matter what the others promise to do,

52
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:52,777
他们根本做不到我所做的承诺
when it comes to the showdown, they won't be there.

53
00:16:54,011 --> 00:16:56,980
坐下!你没有权利...
Sit down! Sit down, you have no right...

54
00:16:57,849 --> 00:17:00,042
我们讨论一下这人说的话吧
Let us discuss what the man has to say.

55
00:17:00,152 --> 00:17:02,346
- 你相信他吗？- 我们讨论一下吧
-Prescott, do you trust this man?
-Let's discuss what he has to say.

56
00:17:02,486 --> 00:17:03,321
1911年

57
00:17:03,321 --> 00:17:04,215
- 他的话毫无逻辑 - 他知道什么？我的家当都在那里！
-There's logic to what he's saying.
-How does he know? My lot is there!
1911年

58
00:17:04,215 --> 00:17:07,086
- 他的话毫无逻辑 - 他知道什么？我的家当都在那里！
-There's logic to what he's saying.
-How does he know? My lot is there!

59
00:17:08,527 --> 00:17:11,654
两三年，有可能要十年
Two or three years, it could be ten years!

60
00:17:11,797 --> 00:17:14,924
-我们除了互相争执啥都没有 -看看那里的那口井
-We gain nothing by losing our heads!
-Look at that well out there!

61
00:17:15,032 --> 00:17:16,522
没有人在吵架
Nobody's losing their heads.

62
00:17:17,501 --> 00:17:20,096
你不该到这里的
You have no business being here!

63
00:17:21,038 --> 00:17:23,507
叫那女人坐下
Sit that woman down, sir!

64
00:17:25,176 --> 00:17:26,576
你可以坐下
You can sit down.

65
00:17:26,678 --> 00:17:29,145
普兰优先生，请别走
Mr. Plainview! Please, Mr. Plainview.

66
00:17:30,281 --> 00:17:32,250
不，先生，你要去哪里？
No, Mr. Plainview! No, where are you going?

67
00:17:32,349 --> 00:17:35,443
-我不需要租这块地，谢谢 -可是我们需要你
-l don't need the lease. Thank you.
-But we need you.

68
00:17:35,554 --> 00:17:37,784
这太混乱了，谢谢你拨空给我
Too much confusion. Thank you for your time.

69
00:17:37,888 --> 00:17:39,584
不，没有什么混乱
No, no, there's no confusion.

70
00:17:39,691 --> 00:17:43,387
你们心甘情愿，我才会要这块地
l wouldn't take the lease if you gave it to me as a gift.

71
00:17:54,038 --> 00:17:56,802
班克先生，我不想浪费你的时间
Mr. Bankside, I'm not going to waste your time.

72
00:17:56,942 --> 00:17:59,375
我也会感激你不浪费我的时间
I'd certainly appreciate it if you didn't waste mine.

73
00:17:59,510 --> 00:18:04,210
如果你想跟我签约，我们十天内就能开始凿井
Now, if you wish to sign with me, we
can have a well drilling within 10 days.

74
00:18:04,348 --> 00:18:07,715
你的地在现存油井的北边
Your lot is further north from the discovery well up here.

75
00:18:07,885 --> 00:18:10,445
那表示我们可能得凿深一点
That means we'll probably have to dig deeper.

76
00:18:10,555 --> 00:18:12,954
如果那里的油跟我想的一样多
And if there's as much oil here as l think there is,

77
00:18:13,057 --> 00:18:16,049
就会更难凿，不过一凿到就发了
it'll be harder to reach, but once
we find it, we can take it right out.

78
00:18:16,193 --> 00:18:20,721
动作要快，油很快就会被凿光了
We have to act quickly, because
very soon these fields will be dry.

79
00:18:20,898 --> 00:18:23,196
我要你知道自己想怎么做
l need you to know what you want to do.

80
00:18:23,335 --> 00:18:26,326
由于现存油井的距离
Now, because of the distance from the discovery well,

81
00:18:26,471 --> 00:18:28,701
我付的使用费会少一点
l'll pay you a smaller royalty than you'd get down there

82
00:18:28,839 --> 00:18:32,640
不过我会给你一千美元签约金
but l'm prepared to give you a $ 1,000 bonus on your lot.

83
00:18:32,743 --> 00:18:34,301
你说的使用费是多少？
What kind of royalty are you talking about?

84
00:18:34,412 --> 00:18:38,848
六分之一，加上十天内开凿的保证
One-sixth, plus a guarantee to start drilling within 10 days.

85
00:18:38,983 --> 00:18:42,181
这种条件你在别处绝对找不到
Now, that's something you won't find anywhere else.

86
00:18:51,061 --> 00:18:53,086
夫人，你小孩几岁了？
What age are your children, ma'am?

87
00:18:53,198 --> 00:18:55,132
10岁和12岁
Ten and twelve.

88
00:18:56,034 --> 00:18:59,902
普兰优先生，我有个问题，你太太人呢？
Mr. Plainview, a question, sir. Where is your wife?

89
00:19:02,039 --> 00:19:04,837
她因难产过世了，夫人
She died in childbirth, Mrs. Bankside.

90
00:19:05,977 --> 00:19:08,275
我跟儿子一起相依为命
So it's just me and my son now.

91
00:19:15,153 --> 00:19:17,086
就快喷油了，老板
lt's coming in, boss!

92
00:19:17,454 --> 00:19:19,115
听见没？
Hear it?

93
00:19:45,016 --> 00:19:46,744
普兰优先生？
Mr. Plainview?

94
00:19:46,851 --> 00:19:48,511
什么事？
Yes?

95
00:19:50,322 --> 00:19:52,414
你就是丹尼尔普兰优？
Are you Daniel Plainview?

96
00:19:54,326 --> 00:19:55,792
对
Yes.

97
00:19:57,127 --> 00:19:59,096
有何贵干？
What can l do for you?

98
00:20:00,932 --> 00:20:02,729
你在找油
You look for oil.

99
00:20:03,969 --> 00:20:05,459
没错
That's right.

100
00:20:05,569 --> 00:20:08,596
你花多少钱租用有藏油的土地？
What do you pay for a place that has it?

101
00:20:08,740 --> 00:20:11,731
-看情况 -看什么情况？
-Well, that depends. -What does it depend on?

102
00:20:13,778 --> 00:20:15,575
有很多
On a lot of things.

103
00:20:16,548 --> 00:20:21,541
如果我说我知道一个地方有油，那里的地价钱又便宜
lf l told you l knew a place that had oil
where land could be bought cheaply,

104
00:20:21,653 --> 00:20:24,416
你想这消息值多少钱？
what do you think that would be worth?

105
00:20:25,423 --> 00:20:29,654
我想...你该让我知道你知道什么
l think that you should let me know what you know

106
00:20:29,760 --> 00:20:32,888
然后我们再谈交易的事
and then we'll try and work something out.

107
00:20:34,932 --> 00:20:37,059
-我能坐吗？-请坐
-Can l sit down? -Please.

108
00:20:48,212 --> 00:20:50,510
你隶属于哪个教堂？
What church do you belong to?

109
00:20:56,221 --> 00:20:57,744
我...
l...

110
00:20:59,691 --> 00:21:03,182
我不排斥宗教，我没有特别隶属于哪个教堂
l enjoy all faiths. l don't belong
to one church in particular.

111
00:21:03,294 --> 00:21:07,320
我全都爱，全都喜欢。你是从哪来的？
l like them all. l like everything. Where are you from?

112
00:21:07,432 --> 00:21:11,299
那正是我要卖给你的消息
That would be telling you. That's what l want to sell you.

113
00:21:13,872 --> 00:21:16,396
你在西诺丘做什么？
What are you doing in Signal Hill?

114
00:21:16,540 --> 00:21:18,906
我们有油，地上就会渗油
We have oil, and it seeps through the ground.

115
00:21:19,044 --> 00:21:20,602
你想付钱知道地点吗？
Do you want to pay me to know where it is?

116
00:21:20,711 --> 00:21:23,646
地上有油并不代表地下也有
Just 'cause there's something on the ground
doesn't mean there's anything beneath it.

117
00:21:23,748 --> 00:21:26,478
标准石油为什么买上面的地？
Why did Standard Oil buy up land?

118
00:21:29,054 --> 00:21:30,988
这地方在加州？
ls it in California?

119
00:21:31,855 --> 00:21:34,983
-也许吧 -他们买多少地？
-Maybe. -How much land did they buy?

120
00:21:35,093 --> 00:21:38,493
我比较希望你不要把我当笨蛋
l'd like it better if you didn't think l was stupid.

121
00:21:46,971 --> 00:21:49,302
你为什么来找我？
Why did you come to me?

122
00:21:49,406 --> 00:21:53,707
-你才刚挖到油 -没错
-You just brought this well in. -That's right.

123
00:21:53,845 --> 00:21:58,144
所以，现在给我五百元现金
Yes, so just give me $500 in cash right now

124
00:21:58,282 --> 00:22:00,682
我就让你知道地点
and l'll tell you where it is.

125
00:22:00,818 --> 00:22:03,083
这样吧，我现在就给你一百元
l'll tell you what l'll do, son. l'll give you $ 1 00 now,

126
00:22:03,188 --> 00:22:07,784
如果证明那里值得开凿，我就再给你一千元奖金
and if it proves to be a promising lease,
then give you a $ 1,000 bonus.

127
00:22:07,959 --> 00:22:09,858
六百元
Six hundred dollars.

128
00:22:12,696 --> 00:22:15,597
你再告诉我，你们那里有什么
Tell me one thing to help me decide.
What else have you got up there?

129
00:22:15,700 --> 00:22:17,394
你们种什么？
What do you grow?

130
00:22:17,501 --> 00:22:21,232
我们有个大牧场，但大多是石头
We have a big ranch, but it's mostly rocks.

131
00:22:21,338 --> 00:22:23,807
试过种东西，却只长杂草
Plant things. Nothing will grow but weeds.

132
00:22:23,942 --> 00:22:25,170
你以为上面会长什么？
What makes you think it's up?

133
00:22:25,276 --> 00:22:28,301
那里有硫磺吗？还是碱矿？
ls there sulfur around? Or alkali deposits?

134
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:31,471
附近有碱矿，我不知道硫磺是啥
Alkali nearby. l don't know sulfur.

135
00:22:38,088 --> 00:22:39,953
那是你儿子？
ls that your son?

136
00:22:40,325 --> 00:22:41,791
对
Yes.

137
00:22:42,961 --> 00:22:44,222
- 你好 - 你好
-Hi. -Hi.

138
00:22:47,432 --> 00:22:50,265
-你是谁？-我是费契汉弥顿
-Who are you? -l'm Fletcher Hamilton.

139
00:22:50,401 --> 00:22:52,368
幸会，孩子，你叫什么名字？
Nice to meet you, son. What's your name?

140
00:22:52,470 --> 00:22:54,403
你是做什么的？
What do you do?

141
00:22:55,105 --> 00:22:57,199
我帮普兰优先生做事
l work with Mr. Plainview.

142
00:22:57,909 --> 00:22:59,672
这里有五百元
Here's $500, son.

143
00:22:59,778 --> 00:23:03,577
你告诉我有价值的消息，这钱就是你的了
You tell me something worth hearing, this money's yours.

144
00:23:07,585 --> 00:23:11,419
我来自伊沙贝郡的小波士顿镇
l come from a town called Little Boston in lsabella County.

145
00:23:13,625 --> 00:23:18,061
就是这里。小波士顿有个铁路支线站
This is us, here. Spur station here at Little Boston.

146
00:23:18,163 --> 00:23:21,132
你要找的就是桑德牧场
The Sunday ranch is what you're looking for.

147
00:23:21,266 --> 00:23:23,461
有一条羊肠小径通到那里
There's a sheep trail that takes you there.

148
00:23:23,601 --> 00:23:26,569
由镇上往西走一哩，不远
lt's a mile out of town headed west, not far.

149
00:23:26,703 --> 00:23:30,571
只要走山脚下这条小路
Just through a small pass here near the base of the hills.

150
00:23:30,741 --> 00:23:34,404
你会经过教堂，沿着小径走就行
You'll pass a church and just follow the sheep trail.

151
00:23:34,578 --> 00:23:38,709
-标准石油买下哪里？ -这里和这里
-Where's Standard buying up? -Here and here.

152
00:23:40,884 --> 00:23:43,285
-你姓桑德？ -对
-Your family name is Sunday, yes? -That's right.

153
00:23:43,421 --> 00:23:44,911
你家有多少人？
How many's in your family?

154
00:23:45,022 --> 00:23:48,185
父母、妹妹和我弟弟伊莱
My father and mother and sisters and my brother Eli.

155
00:23:48,358 --> 00:23:51,020
-你有几个妹妹？ -两个
-How many sisters do you have? -Two.

156
00:23:51,128 --> 00:23:53,426
-你叫什么名字？ -保罗
-What's your name? -Paul.

157
00:23:53,565 --> 00:23:56,761
你家人知道石油的存在吗？
Does any of your family know about the oil that you say is there?

158
00:23:56,901 --> 00:23:58,334
我不知道
l don't know.

159
00:23:58,435 --> 00:24:01,029
我叔叔一直说有石油
My uncle always said there was oil there,

160
00:24:01,205 --> 00:24:03,673
但我不知道他们的想法
but l don't know what they heard or what they think.

161
00:24:03,775 --> 00:24:05,173
你们种些什么？
What do you grow?

162
00:24:05,276 --> 00:24:10,474
我们养羊，那是养羊的牧场。我说过，那里只长杂草
lt's goats. lt's a goat farm.
l told you, nothing grows but weeds.

163
00:24:10,582 --> 00:24:13,049
-那里有水吗？ -是咸水
-ls there water? -lt's salty.

164
00:24:13,218 --> 00:24:16,550
只要挖井，出来的几乎都是咸水
You drill a well, it's hard not to get saltwater.

165
00:24:18,423 --> 00:24:21,824
我跟你们说，那里有石油
The oil is there. l'm telling you.

166
00:24:26,497 --> 00:24:29,660
-我想走了 -你可以留下过夜
-l want to go now, so... -You can stay tonight.

167
00:24:29,834 --> 00:24:33,861
-不，我想走了，我要走 -听着，保罗
-No, l want to go now. l want to leave.
-Listen, Paul.

168
00:24:35,740 --> 00:24:40,507
如果我大老远跑去那里，却发现你骗我
lf l travel all the way out there
and l find that you've been lying to me,

169
00:24:40,677 --> 00:24:43,271
我会找到你，拿回加倍的钱
l'm going to find you and l'm going
to take more than my money back.

170
00:24:43,381 --> 00:24:45,611
那样可以吗？
ls that all right with you?

171
00:24:45,717 --> 00:24:47,947
-可以，先生 -那么好吧
-Yes, sir. -All right, then.

172
00:24:48,653 --> 00:24:52,782
-祝你们好运，上帝保佑 -你也是，年轻人
-Nice luck to you. God bless.
-And to you, young man.

173
00:26:32,222 --> 00:26:34,213
有人来了
-There's someone coming. -Thank you, Mary.

174
00:26:43,968 --> 00:26:47,494
-晚安 -晚安
-Good evening. -Good evening.

175
00:26:50,074 --> 00:26:53,305
我叫丹尼尔普兰优，这是我儿子
My name's Daniel Plainview. This is my son, H.W.

176
00:26:54,177 --> 00:26:56,942
-你来打猎的？ -猎鹌鹑
-Are you hunting? -Hunting for quail.

177
00:26:57,080 --> 00:26:59,913
听说桑德牧场附近适合扎营
We're told there might be a good place
to camp up near the Sunday ranch.

178
00:27:00,018 --> 00:27:01,883
这里就是桑德牧场，你可以扎营
This is the Sunday ranch. You can camp here.

179
00:27:01,986 --> 00:27:04,682
-谢谢，你有水吗？ -有的
-Thank you. Do you have water? -Yes.

180
00:27:05,722 --> 00:27:07,713
听说几天前这里有地震
We heard there was an earthquake up here a few days ago.

181
00:27:07,825 --> 00:27:09,759
-真的吗？ -是啊
-ls that right? -Yes.

182
00:27:10,560 --> 00:27:14,190
-家里还好？ -很好，谢谢
-Your family? -Yeah, all fine. Thank you.

183
00:27:15,833 --> 00:27:19,269
-你想喝的话，我们有羊奶 -那太好了
-We have goat's milk, if you'd like.
-That would be fine.

184
00:27:21,305 --> 00:27:22,363
那现在
Now,

185
00:27:24,208 --> 00:27:28,234
如果我们把帐棚架在那里，就不会挡到你们的路了
if we set our tent away over there,
we'd be out of your way over there.

186
00:27:28,378 --> 00:27:29,641
可以
That's fine.

187
00:27:29,747 --> 00:27:31,942
露丝，过来帮忙，拿水给他们
Ruth! Help these men and bring them some water.

188
00:27:32,049 --> 00:27:33,983
不行，H.W
No! H.W.

189
00:27:35,353 --> 00:27:38,810
普兰优先生，你现在想喝羊奶吗？
Mr. Plainview, would you like that milk now?

190
00:27:38,955 --> 00:27:43,017
-好的，谢谢 -玛丽，拿些羊奶来给他们
-That would be fine. Thank you.
-Mary! Bring them some milk.

191
00:27:43,126 --> 00:27:44,616
我的家人会帮你架好你的帐棚
My family will help you set up your tent.

192
00:27:44,729 --> 00:27:46,923
不，我们露营要自己动手
No, please. We set ourselves on this camping trip.

193
00:27:47,065 --> 00:27:48,726
我们自己来架帐棚
We have to do the camping.

194
00:27:48,833 --> 00:27:50,424
动作快
Hurry up!

195
00:27:53,171 --> 00:27:57,163
-你有面包吗？ -我们有马铃薯
-Do you have bread? -We have potatoes.

196
00:27:57,307 --> 00:27:58,969
马铃薯就很好了，谢谢
Potatoes would be nice, thank you.

197
00:27:59,076 --> 00:28:00,544
我会叫她们煮些马铃薯给你们
l'll have them boil you up some potatoes.

198
00:28:00,644 --> 00:28:02,942
没关系，我们可以生火来煮
That's all right. l thought maybe we'd make a fire.

199
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:05,310
我想跟我儿子一起合作生火
l wanted to work with my son on making a fire.

200
00:28:05,415 --> 00:28:07,349
我儿子伊莱会拿些柴来给你们
All right. My son, Eli, will bring you some wood.

201
00:28:07,451 --> 00:28:09,510
谢谢你盛情的招待，桑德先生
Thank you so much for your hospitality, Mr. Sunday.

202
00:28:09,619 --> 00:28:11,644
-没问题 -我们不会碍事
-Yes. -And we'll be out of your way.

203
00:28:11,756 --> 00:28:14,486
只是来猎鹌鹑
-We're just hunting for quail. -Yes.

204
00:28:16,461 --> 00:28:18,622
-抱歉我们没有面包 -没关系
-l'm sorry we don't have any bread.
-No, no, no.

205
00:28:18,729 --> 00:28:21,527
这里种不出玉米，全是石头
Corn doesn't fill out in the hills here. lt's mostly rock.

206
00:28:21,632 --> 00:28:24,430
我们没地方可以种谷子
We don't have room to raise the grain.

207
00:28:28,205 --> 00:28:30,230
谢谢你，小姐
Thank you, young lady.

208
00:28:55,500 --> 00:28:57,126
我叫伊莱
My name is Eli.

209
00:28:58,469 --> 00:29:00,596
是的，你是...伊莱桑德
Yes, you're Eli Sunday.

210
00:29:01,404 --> 00:29:03,066
欢迎你们
Welcome.

211
00:29:06,544 --> 00:29:08,478
-H.W. -伊莱
-H.W. -Eli.

212
00:29:13,550 --> 00:29:16,644
-你们来猎鹌鹑？ -是的
-You're hunting quail? -That's right.

213
00:29:20,892 --> 00:29:25,420
-我们会拿晚餐过来 -谢谢，真感谢你
-We will bring dinner. -Thank you. Thank you so much.

214
00:30:47,510 --> 00:30:49,035
爸!
Dad!

215
00:30:49,413 --> 00:30:51,142
看我的鞋子
Dad, look at my shoe.

216
00:31:17,642 --> 00:31:20,269
那是地震震出来的油，别激动
That's earthquake oil. Set loose.

217
00:31:43,800 --> 00:31:45,393
所以...
So...

218
00:31:46,703 --> 00:31:48,296
所以？
So?

219
00:31:48,772 --> 00:31:50,501
是啊，所以
So, so.

220
00:31:50,941 --> 00:31:54,240
这里若有油，我们就运到海边
If there's anything here, we take it to the sea.

221
00:31:55,346 --> 00:31:59,112
拉输油管到怀尼米港或圣宝拉
What we do is we build a pipeline
to Port Hueneme or Santa Paula,

222
00:31:59,215 --> 00:32:00,740
大约有一百哩
it's about 100 miles,

223
00:32:00,851 --> 00:32:04,752
我们再跟联合石油谈交易，这一行就是这样
and we do a deal with Union Oil. This is what we do.

224
00:32:05,288 --> 00:32:08,258
之后我们就不需要铁路还有运送成本了
Then we don't need the railroads
and their shipping costs anymore.

225
00:32:08,358 --> 00:32:09,951
懂吧？
You see?

226
00:32:12,596 --> 00:32:13,653
懂
Yeah.

227
00:32:13,763 --> 00:32:16,425
-你懂了？ -我懂
-You see that? -Yeah.

228
00:32:17,468 --> 00:32:19,731
那样我们就能赚钱，赚大钱
Then we're making money. We're making the real money.

229
00:32:19,836 --> 00:32:21,701
那也是我们该赚的
What we should be making. Not just...

230
00:32:21,806 --> 00:32:24,137
不是把赚的钱浪费在运送上
Not just throwing it away on shipping costs.

231
00:32:24,307 --> 00:32:26,434
那样赚的就太少了
Otherwise, it's just mud.

232
00:32:30,647 --> 00:32:33,241
我们要付他们多少？
How much are we going to pay them?

233
00:32:34,117 --> 00:32:35,846
他们是谁？
Who's that?

234
00:32:38,288 --> 00:32:40,086
桑德家
The Sunday family.

235
00:32:40,657 --> 00:32:43,558
我不会给他们油田价
l'm not going to give them oil prices.

236
00:32:46,096 --> 00:32:48,394
我会给他们鹌鹑价
l'll give them quail prices.

237
00:32:54,105 --> 00:32:55,766
我想跟你们谈一下
lf we could take a few minutes,

238
00:32:55,873 --> 00:32:59,000
有件事我想跟你谈谈
there's something l'd very much like to talk with you about.

239
00:32:59,109 --> 00:33:02,442
孩子的妈，带女孩子们出去
Mother, would you take the girls outside, please?

240
00:33:14,692 --> 00:33:17,422
我说话不喜欢拐弯抹角
l believe in plain speaking, so...

241
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:21,258
这牧场很美，我喜欢猎鹌鹑
This is a beautiful ranch. l love hunting for quail.

242
00:33:22,133 --> 00:33:25,192
我儿子有病，他需要新鲜空气
My boy has been sick, you know. He needs fresh air.

243
00:33:25,301 --> 00:33:28,532
医生说他需要大量的新鲜空气
Doctors all say he needs plentiful fresh air.

244
00:33:30,340 --> 00:33:31,432
那
So,

245
00:33:33,943 --> 00:33:37,903
你想这块地的值多少钱？
what would you say would be
a fair price for this lot, Abel?

246
00:33:39,016 --> 00:33:41,576
-买下这里？ -是的
-To buy this place? -That's right.

247
00:33:46,624 --> 00:33:48,386
想一下
Take a moment.

248
00:33:52,262 --> 00:33:56,028
- 对不起，我不知道 - 一备六元
-l'm sorry. l don't know. -Six dollars an acre.

249
00:33:56,133 --> 00:33:59,568
六元？谢谢，伊莱
Six dollars? Thank you, Eli.

250
00:33:59,702 --> 00:34:03,365
还有加上多年来 用来改良牧场的五百元
And then with the improvements
to the ranch over the years at $500...

251
00:34:03,540 --> 00:34:06,031
我想出三千七买这个牧场
l'd like to offer you $3,700 for this ranch.

252
00:34:06,210 --> 00:34:08,735
-就是三千七百元 -不行
-That's $3,700. -No.

253
00:34:09,713 --> 00:34:12,010
上帝派这人来此，伊莱
The Lord has sent this man here, Eli.

254
00:34:12,115 --> 00:34:13,639
是的，我相信是的
Yes, l believe He has.

255
00:34:13,751 --> 00:34:17,811
-我出价三千七百元 -是什么引你来此的？
-My offer to you is $3,700.
-What is it that brought you here, sir?

256
00:34:19,023 --> 00:34:20,684
万能上帝的指引
The Good Lord's guidance.

257
00:34:20,791 --> 00:34:23,853
当然，之后我们可以租地给你
-Now, of course, within that... -What about our oil?
...we're going to develop a lease.

258
00:34:25,195 --> 00:34:28,688
-你说呢？ -那我们的石油呢？
-What's that? -What about our oil?

259
00:34:30,067 --> 00:34:31,500
什么石油？
What about it?

260
00:34:31,601 --> 00:34:33,831
我们这里有石油，那很值钱
We have oil here. That's worth something.

261
00:34:33,938 --> 00:34:36,338
你们有人会钻探石油？
Do you have someone who can drill for it?

262
00:34:36,440 --> 00:34:38,431
-你认为这里有石油？ -我相信有
-Do you think there's oil here? -l know there is.

263
00:34:38,541 --> 00:34:40,532
钻油费用是很昂贵的
lt's very expensive to drill.

264
00:34:40,710 --> 00:34:42,871
把油从地底弄出来，你试过吗？
To get it up and out of the ground.
You ever tried that before?

265
00:34:42,980 --> 00:34:45,039
-那要多少钱？ -很贵
-How much is it? -Costly.

266
00:34:45,148 --> 00:34:48,175
我们的油在地上就有
Well, our oil sits right up on top of the ground.

267
00:34:49,219 --> 00:34:51,016
我想那是渗出来的
l believe that's called seepage.

268
00:34:51,121 --> 00:34:52,644
并不必然意味底下有东西
Doesn't necessarily mean there's anything underneath.

269
00:34:52,755 --> 00:34:54,916
-你出多少钱买油？ -我不知道
-What would you give us for it? -l don't know.

270
00:34:55,025 --> 00:34:57,925
-你也有不知道的 -是啊
-Something you don't know. -That's right.

271
00:35:01,264 --> 00:35:03,233
你要多少？
What would you like, Eli?

272
00:35:04,934 --> 00:35:07,233
一万
Ten thousand dollars.

273
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:11,101
为什么？
For what?

274
00:35:12,909 --> 00:35:14,775
为了我的教堂
For my church.

275
00:35:24,554 --> 00:35:26,045
有趣
That's good.

276
00:35:29,059 --> 00:35:30,856
真是有趣
That's a good one.

277
00:35:32,496 --> 00:35:33,588
那
Well...

278
00:35:34,731 --> 00:35:38,360
要是我们决定钻探石油，若油井量产
lf we decide to drill for oil and if the well begins to produce,

279
00:35:38,469 --> 00:35:40,096
我就给你的教堂五千元的签约金
l'll give your church a $5,000 signing bonus.

280
00:35:40,204 --> 00:35:41,262
一万
Ten thousand.

281
00:35:41,371 --> 00:35:43,840
你想找别人来这里钻油？
Do you want to find someone else
that's going to come here and drill, Eli?

282
00:35:43,940 --> 00:35:47,001
找别人投资兼做苦工？
Make the investment and do
all the hard work that goes into it?

283
00:35:47,143 --> 00:35:51,012
我去别的牧场也能猎鹌鹑
l can just as easily hunt for quail
on another ranch as l can here, so...

284
00:35:51,148 --> 00:35:55,811
虽然我很乐意支持你的教堂
Though l'll happily be a supporter
of your church for as long as l can.

285
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:57,682
只有红利
For the bonus only.

286
00:35:59,523 --> 00:36:03,322
很巧的是，我刚好在钻油业有认识人
Now, as it happens, l do have some
connections in the drilling business

287
00:36:03,427 --> 00:36:07,989
他们也许能帮我们起头。你觉得如何，亚伯？
who might help get us started.
How do you feel about this, Abel?

288
00:36:08,097 --> 00:36:09,998
好，伊莱说什么都好
Yes. What Eli says.

289
00:36:10,099 --> 00:36:15,304
很好，我们先签个约来试试
Well, good! Let's draw up
some contracts and let's... Let's give it a try.

290
00:36:16,673 --> 00:36:19,472
多谢你的帮忙，伊莱
Appreciate your help with this, Eli.

291
00:36:30,820 --> 00:36:32,447
-午安 -午安
-Good afternoon. -Good afternoon.

292
00:36:32,556 --> 00:36:33,887
-仲介？-对
-Real estate? -Yes.

293
00:36:33,990 --> 00:36:35,958
是的，我想跟你谈谈
Yes, l'd like to talk to you.

294
00:36:36,092 --> 00:36:40,586
我在找土地，我刚买下桑德牧场
l'm looking for some land. l just bought the Sunday ranch.

295
00:36:40,731 --> 00:36:44,757
然后...地图在哪？
And, well, where's the map?

296
00:36:45,335 --> 00:36:47,769
桑德牧场后的丘陵地在哪？
Where are the hills behind the Sunday ranch?

297
00:36:47,905 --> 00:36:51,601
在这里，那是班迪的地。他有六百多备
That's here. lt's the Bandy tract. He has over 600 acres.

298
00:36:51,708 --> 00:36:55,735
班迪，六百备
Bandy, 600.

299
00:36:55,878 --> 00:37:02,340
-这里呢？ -毛德、布洛杰、瑞狄、卡尔
-What about this?
-A.C. Maude, Blodget, Redlick, Carr.

300
00:37:04,054 --> 00:37:07,079
-现在的地租多少？ -一备六元
-What's it held at? -Six dollars an acre.

301
00:37:07,791 --> 00:37:09,121
六元
Six.

302
00:37:09,226 --> 00:37:10,887
这里呢？
What about this?

303
00:37:10,994 --> 00:37:14,556
北文家的，那很好买，我保证
That's the Belvins', and that could be got, l'm sure.

304
00:37:16,467 --> 00:37:19,163
这附近的地都能买下吗？
Can everything around here be got?

305
00:37:19,936 --> 00:37:21,403
行
Sure.

306
00:37:45,728 --> 00:37:49,186
保罗桑德成了我们的好朋友
Paul Sunday turned out to be a good friend of ours.

307
00:37:49,900 --> 00:37:51,458
没错
That's right.

308
00:37:53,836 --> 00:37:57,829
你尽快赶到这里，把佛雷英格带来
Well, you get here just as soon
as you can. Bring Fred English.

309
00:37:59,208 --> 00:38:00,733
好了
Good enough.

310
00:38:01,311 --> 00:38:03,039
谢谢
Thank you, porter.

311
00:38:05,648 --> 00:38:08,277
-H.W.，你好吗？ -很好，你呢？
-H.W., how are you? -Fine, and you?

312
00:38:08,418 --> 00:38:10,284
- 很不错，你爸呢？- 他在里面
-Pretty good. Where's your dad? -He's inside.

313
00:38:10,387 --> 00:38:11,820
你们从西诺丘大老远赶来了
You fellas are a long way from Signal Hill.

314
00:38:11,922 --> 00:38:13,913
-你好，普兰优 -你好，金
-Hello, Plainview. -Hello, Gene.

315
00:38:14,023 --> 00:38:16,485
-真高兴见到你 -查理
-Good to see you. -Charlie.

316
00:38:16,626 --> 00:38:21,155
-要去别的地方？ -经过，四处看看
-On your way somewhere else?
-Passing through. Looking around.

317
00:38:21,297 --> 00:38:23,822
-看到你真怪 -是很怪，不是吗？
-Funny to see you. -Funny, isn't it?

318
00:38:23,934 --> 00:38:26,664
你们是标准的家族事业
You boys are a regular family business.

319
00:38:26,836 --> 00:38:28,498
你们来的有点晚了
You boys are a little late.

320
00:38:28,605 --> 00:38:32,632
-你找到什么了？ -我找到一些有趣的东西
-What did you find?
-l found some interesting prospects.

321
00:38:32,775 --> 00:38:34,003
听说标准石油买地了？
Did you hear Standard bought up?

322
00:38:34,110 --> 00:38:36,739
-大多是北边的地 -我听说的也是
-Mostly in the north, so far.
-That's what l hear.

323
00:38:36,880 --> 00:38:40,246
金，如果你想买地，往东去
l'm gonna tell you, Gene,
if you're gonna make a play, look east.

324
00:38:40,416 --> 00:38:45,650
我宁可是你买下那里。这附近的地都被买下了
l'd rather it be you than someone else.
This mud around here has been taken.

325
00:38:45,822 --> 00:38:49,315
有这个小帅哥在身边，谈买卖一定更顺利
lt must be easy when you have such
a cute face to carry around with you.

326
00:38:49,425 --> 00:38:52,519
-你是想说我儿子很帅？ -正是
-Telling me how handsome my son is?
-Well, that l am.

327
00:38:52,663 --> 00:38:55,791
你真好，谢谢，祝你好运
That's very nice. Thank you. Good luck, Gene.

328
00:38:55,932 --> 00:38:58,423
-保重 -我说过，往东边去
-Take care. -Like l said, go east.

329
00:38:58,534 --> 00:38:59,592
H.W.

330
00:39:00,637 --> 00:39:03,298
你若要签约，可以找我当律师
l'll be your lawyer if you need to draw up a contract.

331
00:39:03,407 --> 00:39:07,706
我能确保你不会被骗，帮你弄到你爸一半的利润
Make sure you don't get swindled, boy.
Get half what your dad's making.

332
00:39:17,987 --> 00:39:19,579
怎样？
How's that?

333
00:39:34,538 --> 00:39:36,664
那些人在干嘛？
What are those men doing?

334
00:39:39,041 --> 00:39:41,567
他们是帮我们工作的人
They're just guys that are working for us.

335
00:39:41,711 --> 00:39:43,976
他们只是四处看看
They're just looking around.

336
00:39:46,182 --> 00:39:48,447
我们能赚多少钱？
How much money can we make?

337
00:39:52,489 --> 00:39:54,820
不知道，要看情况
l don't know. lt depends.

338
00:39:59,061 --> 00:40:01,121
一千元？
One thousand dollars?

339
00:40:09,005 --> 00:40:12,771
玛丽说若她不祷告，她爸就打她
Mary said that her father beats her if she doesn't pray.

340
00:40:19,349 --> 00:40:21,817
玛丽，年纪比较小的那个？
Mary, she's the smaller one?

341
00:40:24,454 --> 00:40:26,182
对，就是她
Yes, she is.

342
00:40:39,769 --> 00:40:42,295
-都到齐了？ -非常成功
-Everyone here? -Very successful.

343
00:40:43,072 --> 00:40:44,130
可是？
But?

344
00:40:44,240 --> 00:40:47,574
有几块地找不到地主
There were a few vacant lots
and one holdout.

345
00:40:47,744 --> 00:40:49,405
-是谁的？ -威廉班迪
-Who? -William Bandy.

346
00:40:49,512 --> 00:40:51,538
他是谁？
...eight. Who's he?

347
00:40:51,681 --> 00:40:53,081
他在这里务农
He's an old man who homesteaded here.

348
00:40:53,182 --> 00:40:56,242
跟孙子一起住，他想跟你谈谈
Lives with his grandson. He said he'd like to speak with you.

349
00:40:56,420 --> 00:40:57,614
他来了？
ls he here?

350
00:40:57,721 --> 00:41:00,713
不，他要你去找他
No, he'd like you to come visit with him.

351
00:41:00,891 --> 00:41:02,619
他要抬高价钱
He's boosting his price.

352
00:41:02,726 --> 00:41:06,525
他说他想跟收买土地的人谈
He said he'd like to speak with whoever is doing the buying.

353
00:41:06,663 --> 00:41:09,893
让他等着，他会找上门的，走吧
Well, let him wait. He'll come around. Let's go.

354
00:41:16,940 --> 00:41:18,873
各位？
Ladies and gentlemen?

355
00:41:19,909 --> 00:41:21,900
各位
Ladies and gentlemen.

356
00:41:22,079 --> 00:41:25,445
谢谢你们今晚大驾光临
Thank you so much for visiting with us this evening.

357
00:41:25,581 --> 00:41:29,143
我跨越了大半的北达克达州来到这里，来看看这块土地
Now, l've traveled across half our state
to be here and to see about this land.

358
00:41:32,222 --> 00:41:33,746
我敢说你们有人可能听说过
Now, I daresay some of you might have heard

359
00:41:33,856 --> 00:41:37,690
一些更夸张的谣言，传说我有些什么计划
some of the more extravagant rumors
about what my plans are,

360
00:41:37,827 --> 00:41:40,523
我只是认为你们该亲耳听我说
so I just thought you'd like to hear it from me.

361
00:41:40,697 --> 00:41:43,530
就是这张脸，没什么神秘的
This is the face. It's no great mystery.

362
00:41:46,402 --> 00:41:50,362
我是个石油商人，各位
I'm an oilman, ladies and gentlemen,

363
00:41:51,240 --> 00:41:54,677
我对许多地方都有兴趣
I have numerous concerns spread across this state.

364
00:41:54,811 --> 00:41:58,177
我有很多油井每天产出数千桶油
I have many wells flowing
at many thousand barrels per day,

365
00:41:58,315 --> 00:42:01,250
所以我认为我是个石油商
so I like to think of myself as an oilman.

366
00:42:02,219 --> 00:42:04,016
身为石油商
As an oilman, I hope that you'll forgive

367
00:42:04,153 --> 00:42:07,021
我希望各位原谅我有话直说
just good old-fashioned plain speaking.

368
00:42:08,692 --> 00:42:12,184
我们做的是家族事业
Now, this work that we do
is very much a family enterprise.

369
00:42:12,362 --> 00:42:14,989
我跟我儿子H.W.携手合作
I work side by side with my wonderful son, H. W.

370
00:42:15,132 --> 00:42:18,329
我想你们有人可能见过他了
I think one or two of you might have met him already.

371
00:42:18,467 --> 00:42:22,233
我也鼓励我的手下带家人一起来
And I encourage my men to bring their families, as well.

372
00:42:22,371 --> 00:42:26,331
当然，这么做有助于促进他们获得更有价值的人生
Of course, it makes for an ever
so much more rewarding life for them.

373
00:42:26,476 --> 00:42:30,411
家庭代表孩子，孩子代表教育
Family means children, and children means education.

374
00:42:30,514 --> 00:42:34,177
所以，不管我们落脚何处，教育是必要的
So, wherever we set up camp, education is a necessity,

375
00:42:34,351 --> 00:42:36,512
我们也很高兴能满足需求
and we're just so happy to take care of that.

376
00:42:36,686 --> 00:42:39,052
让我们在小波士顿造一间学校
So let's build a wonderful school in Little Boston.

377
00:42:39,188 --> 00:42:41,418
这些孩子是我们努力的未来
These children are the future that we strive for,

378
00:42:41,525 --> 00:42:44,619
所以他们也该拥有最好的
and so they should have the very best of things.

379
00:42:44,760 --> 00:42:46,728
现在，还有一件事
Now, something else,

380
00:42:46,829 --> 00:42:50,664
请别误会我有侮蔑的意思：面包
and please don't be insulted
if l speak about this. Bread.

381
00:42:50,833 --> 00:42:52,802
我们来谈谈面包吧
Let's talk about bread.

382
00:42:53,503 --> 00:42:56,802
在我看来，我很讨厌去想到
Now, to my mind, it's an abomination to consider

383
00:42:56,974 --> 00:43:01,137
有任何男人、女人、或小孩，在我们这个伟大的国家里
that any man, woman, or child
in this magnificent country of ours

384
00:43:01,311 --> 00:43:04,768
竟然将一条面包视为是奢侈品
should have to look upon a loaf of bread as a luxury.

385
00:43:05,581 --> 00:43:09,108
我们要在这里挖水井，而水井就代表灌溉
We're going to dig water wells here,
and water wells means irrigation.

386
00:43:09,286 --> 00:43:11,617
灌溉就意味着耕种
Irrigation means cultivation.

387
00:43:11,788 --> 00:43:15,621
我们要在这里种谷子，在这之前一片荒芜的土地上
We're going to raise crops here where
before it just simply wasn't possible.

388
00:43:15,791 --> 00:43:18,192
你们会有更多的谷子可以运用
You're going to have more grain
than you'll know what to do with,

389
00:43:18,295 --> 00:43:21,264
面包会多到你吃不完，夫人
and bread will be coming right out of your ears, ma'am.

390
00:43:21,398 --> 00:43:26,664
新的道路、农业、就业、教育
New roads, agriculture, employment, education.

391
00:43:26,802 --> 00:43:28,793
这些只是改进的一小部份
These are just a few of the things we can offer you,

392
00:43:28,905 --> 00:43:30,873
各位，我向你们保证
and l assure you, ladies and gentlemen,

393
00:43:30,974 --> 00:43:33,101
若我们真在此找到石油
that if we do find oil here,

394
00:43:33,275 --> 00:43:36,677
我想我们很有可能会找到
and l think there's a very good chance that we will,

395
00:43:36,813 --> 00:43:41,273
你们的社区将不再贫瘠，它将兴隆繁盛
this community of yours
will not only survive, it will flourish.

396
00:43:43,552 --> 00:43:46,579
我很乐意回答任何问题，请说？
l'd be happy to answer any questions
that you might have. Yes?

397
00:43:46,722 --> 00:43:49,213
新的道路会通往教堂吗？
Will the new road lead to the church?

398
00:43:49,358 --> 00:43:53,762
那会是第一个通往的地方。谢谢你，伊莱，还有谁？
That'll be the first place that it leads.
Thank you, Eli. Anyone else?

399
00:43:54,431 --> 00:43:56,762
如果有任何事，我很容易找的
Well, if anything comes up, l'm pretty easy to find.

400
00:43:56,867 --> 00:43:58,128
你们随时可以来找我
You just come visit with me.

401
00:43:58,235 --> 00:44:00,226
谢谢各位宝贵的时间，晚安
Thank you so much for your time, and good night.

402
00:44:38,809 --> 00:44:43,711
“何等权利能将万事”
What a privilege to carry

403
00:44:43,880 --> 00:44:47,713
“来到耶稣座前求”
everything to God in prayer!

404
00:44:48,717 --> 00:44:52,278
“何等权利能将万事”
What a privilege to carry...

405
00:45:09,639 --> 00:45:11,539
只要沿着通往教堂的新路
Just follow the new road
right to the church.

406
00:45:11,641 --> 00:45:13,835
新的路会引领你们过去
The new road will lead you there.

407
00:45:13,976 --> 00:45:15,672
兄弟，你好，我叫伊莱
Hello, brother, my name is Eli.

408
00:45:15,778 --> 00:45:19,271
第三启示教堂欢迎你
The Church of the Third Revelation
welcomes you.

409
00:45:19,449 --> 00:45:21,177
兄弟，你好，我叫伊莱
Hello, brother, my name is Eli.

410
00:45:21,284 --> 00:45:23,581
第三启示教堂欢迎你
The Church of the Third Revelation
welcomes you.

411
00:45:23,686 --> 00:45:26,679
沿着新路走就能抵达教堂
Just follow the new road
right to the church.

412
00:45:35,599 --> 00:45:39,126
“我们弱点主都知透”
Jesus knows our every weakness

413
00:45:40,971 --> 00:45:43,905
“放心到主座前求”
Take it to the Lord in prayer

414
00:45:45,141 --> 00:45:49,306
“劳苦多愁软弱不堪”
Are we weak and heavy-laden

415
00:45:50,347 --> 00:45:53,373
“挂虑重担压肩头”
Cumbered with a load of care?

416
00:45:54,583 --> 00:45:57,711
“主是你我避难处所”
Precious Savior still our refuge

417
00:45:59,755 --> 00:46:02,315
“快到主恩座前求”
Take it to the Lord in prayer...

418
00:46:14,336 --> 00:46:17,396
-丹尼尔，我能跟你谈谈吗？ -可以，请进
-Daniel, may l speak with you?
-Yes, come in.

419
00:46:19,576 --> 00:46:22,545
他们一到我就带过来
l'll bring them up when they arrive.

420
00:46:22,646 --> 00:46:24,876
-早 -早
-Good morning. -Good morning.

421
00:46:24,981 --> 00:46:26,880
工程进度如何？
How is all the work coming?

422
00:46:27,050 --> 00:46:28,483
很顺利
Everything's good.

423
00:46:28,585 --> 00:46:31,679
-人手充足？ -当然
-All the men are provided for? -Of course.

424
00:46:33,757 --> 00:46:35,621
充满干劲
Spirits seem high.

425
00:46:38,094 --> 00:46:41,530
有什么需要我帮忙的吗？
ls there anything that you need from me?

426
00:46:44,634 --> 00:46:48,865
-任何教堂能帮得上的忙？ -我想没有，谢谢
-Anything the church can do for you?
-l don't believe so. No. Thank you.

427
00:46:49,039 --> 00:46:51,336
我知道你明天邀请大家
l understand you've asked the people to gather around

428
00:46:51,474 --> 00:46:53,101
来此观看开井仪式
and watch the well begin tomorrow. ls that right?

429
00:46:53,210 --> 00:46:55,177
- 是 - 我会为这口井祈福
-That's right. -l will bless the well.

430
00:46:56,913 --> 00:46:59,608
在你开始之前，你该介绍我
Before you begin, you should introduce me.

431
00:46:59,748 --> 00:47:02,309
你会看到我走向油井，然后...
You'll see me walk up
towards the oil well, and when l...

432
00:47:02,418 --> 00:47:03,476
是油井塔
The derrick.

433
00:47:03,586 --> 00:47:07,353
你会看到我走出来，然后你可以说出我的名字
You'll see me walk up,
and then you could say my name.

434
00:47:07,523 --> 00:47:09,650
你走出来？
When you walk up?

435
00:47:09,759 --> 00:47:13,661
对，你会看到我走出来，然后你可以说...
Yes. You'll see me walk up,
and then you could say,

436
00:47:13,896 --> 00:47:18,891
“看顾上帝子民的本土之子”
''The proud son of these hills
who tended his Father's flock,''

437
00:47:19,135 --> 00:47:21,501
然后你可以说出我的名字
and then you could say my name.

438
00:47:22,806 --> 00:47:24,398
很好
That's fine.

439
00:47:25,375 --> 00:47:28,775
-接着会怎样？ -接着我们就开始钻油
-And what happens then?
-Well, then we start the drill.

440
00:47:31,947 --> 00:47:35,577
这是简单的祈福，不过却很重要
lt's a simple blessing, Daniel, but an important one.

441
00:47:35,751 --> 00:47:38,721
只有几句话，不会太久
lt's just a few words. lt won't take long.

442
00:47:39,789 --> 00:47:42,882
-什么时候？ -你们什么时候方便？
-What time? -What time's good for you, Eli?

443
00:47:43,025 --> 00:47:45,858
-四点 -那就四点吧
-4:00. -Well, let's make it 4:00 then.

444
00:47:46,929 --> 00:47:50,695
-很感谢你来访 -祝你愉快，谢谢
-My thanks for your visit. -Good day. Thank you.

445
00:48:06,081 --> 00:48:08,050
各位午安
Afternoon, everyone.

446
00:48:09,385 --> 00:48:11,012
跟我来
Come with me.

447
00:48:16,393 --> 00:48:19,851
感谢各位在这个时刻来访
l thank you all so much for visiting with us at this time.

448
00:48:20,030 --> 00:48:21,827
我很荣幸见过你们其中几位
l've had the pleasure of meeting some of you

449
00:48:21,931 --> 00:48:23,762
希望接下来的日子里
and l hope very much in the months to come,

450
00:48:23,867 --> 00:48:27,030
我能拜访你们每一个人
l'll be able to visit with each and every one of you.

451
00:48:27,202 --> 00:48:29,831
我擅长钻凿却不善演说
l'm better at digging holes in the
ground than making speeches,

452
00:48:30,005 --> 00:48:31,563
所以今晚略过演说
so let's forget the speech for this evening,

453
00:48:31,675 --> 00:48:33,539
直接祈祷吧
just make it a simple blessing.

454
00:48:33,710 --> 00:48:35,472
要明白，钻油不能只靠一个人
You see, one man doesn't prospect from the ground.

455
00:48:35,577 --> 00:48:39,480
这要靠一整个社区的善良百姓，像各位
lt takes a whole community of
good people, such as yourselves,

456
00:48:39,581 --> 00:48:42,608
而这很不错，我们齐聚一堂
and this is good. We stay together.

457
00:48:42,719 --> 00:48:44,481
我们一起祷告、工作
We pray together, we work together,

458
00:48:44,586 --> 00:48:47,521
若上帝对我们的努力微笑以待
and if the Good Lord smiles kindly on our endeavor,

459
00:48:47,690 --> 00:48:50,159
我们就共享财富
we share in the wealth together.

460
00:48:52,561 --> 00:48:54,621
在玛丽一号井开工前
Now, before we spud in Mary's Well Number One,

461
00:48:54,731 --> 00:48:57,927
这井以我身旁的玛丽桑德命名
named for the lovely
Miss Mary Sunday, here by my side,

462
00:48:58,034 --> 00:49:01,003
在地的本土之女
a proud daughter of these hills,

463
00:49:01,170 --> 00:49:04,833
我想说，上帝保佑真诚的工人，当然，还有
l'd just like to say God bless these
honest labors of ours, and, of course,

464
00:49:04,974 --> 00:49:06,998
上帝保佑各位
God bless you all.

465
00:49:07,143 --> 00:49:08,268
阿门
Amen.

466
00:49:08,378 --> 00:49:09,902
去吧
Now go.

467
00:49:14,650 --> 00:49:16,414
很快就开始
Won't be a minute.

468
00:49:19,456 --> 00:49:21,423
快点，H.W
Fast as you can, H.W.

469
00:49:24,960 --> 00:49:27,088
准备好了？
Are you ready to do this?

470
00:49:36,940 --> 00:49:39,407
动工了，各位
That's it, ladies and gentlemen!

471
00:49:43,278 --> 00:49:47,409
艾尔罗斯很慷慨的为这个典礼自掏腰包的
Al Rose has very generously provided
some refreshments for this occasion

472
00:49:47,516 --> 00:49:50,213
提供了一些点心，谢谢你
out of his own pocket. Thank you, Al.

473
00:49:50,954 --> 00:49:55,391
请各位自便，我马上回来
lf you'll all just care to help yourselves,
l'll be back in a minute.

474
00:51:08,364 --> 00:51:09,922
玛丽
Mary.

475
00:51:11,568 --> 00:51:13,195
玛丽桑德
Mary Sunday.

476
00:51:16,039 --> 00:51:18,768
-你喜欢你的新衣服吗？ -喜欢，谢谢
-Do you like your new dress?
-Yes. Thank you.

477
00:51:18,875 --> 00:51:21,775
不用客气，我就觉得你会喜欢
You're welcome. l thought you'd like it.

478
00:51:22,644 --> 00:51:25,170
-你高兴我来这里吗？ -高兴
-Are you happy l came here? -Yes.

479
00:51:26,882 --> 00:51:30,614
你爸没再打你了吧？他有吗？
Your daddy doesn't hit you anymore,
does he? Does he now?

480
00:51:31,487 --> 00:51:33,478
最好是没有，对吧？
Better not, right?

481
00:51:34,023 --> 00:51:36,014
我会照顾你的
l'll take care of you.

482
00:51:37,092 --> 00:51:42,224
不再被打了，对吧？不再被打了，去吧
No more hitting, right? No more hitting. Now go.

483
00:51:42,364 --> 00:51:45,425
去多玩一下，不用再回来了
Go and play some more
and don't come back.

484
00:51:54,543 --> 00:51:56,204
丹尼尔？
Daniel?

485
00:51:59,648 --> 00:52:03,813
没事，H.W.，回去睡吧。去吧，快回去睡
lt's okay, H.W. Go back to sleep.
Go on. Go back to sleep.

486
00:52:06,356 --> 00:52:07,516
丹尼尔
Daniel.

487
00:52:09,958 --> 00:52:11,119
丹尼尔
Daniel.

488
00:52:14,063 --> 00:52:15,324
丹尼尔
Daniel!

489
00:52:16,932 --> 00:52:18,092
丹尼尔
Daniel!

490
00:52:18,201 --> 00:52:19,793
怎样？
What?

491
00:52:21,336 --> 00:52:23,429
井里死了一个人
Lost a man down the well.

492
00:52:27,976 --> 00:52:30,103
-哪一个？ -乔根达
-What man? -Joe Gundha.

493
00:52:32,114 --> 00:52:34,309
-我认识他吗？ -不认识
-Did l know him? -No.

494
00:52:34,684 --> 00:52:35,742
怎么回事？
What happened?

495
00:52:43,425 --> 00:52:45,018
拉起来
Pick it up.

496
00:52:45,494 --> 00:52:47,086
拉刹车
Set the brake.

497
00:52:47,230 --> 00:52:49,527
-绑起来 -绑好
-Tie it down. -Tie it on.

498
00:52:54,103 --> 00:52:55,626
糟了
Shit!

499
00:52:57,507 --> 00:53:00,340
该死，遗体呢？
God damn it. Where's the body?

500
00:53:00,643 --> 00:53:03,668
-他们正在找 -好
-They're fishing it out now. -All right.

501
00:53:07,050 --> 00:53:09,677
-钻头呢？ -在台子上
-Where's the bit? -lt's on the deck.

502
00:53:53,195 --> 00:53:56,028
清理一下，帮他换衣服
Clean him up. Put some clothes on him.

503
00:53:57,199 --> 00:53:58,461
然后
And...

